"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985017","Department for Transport","false","2018-10-24","<p>Ministers and officials have met UK port-owning companies on numerous occasions to discuss preparations for exiting the European Union. This includes various port visits by Ministers from the Department for Transport and other Departments, and officials' meetings involving ports under the aegis of the Border Delivery Group, including a systematic programme of engagement by Border Force with all UK ports engaged in international trade.</p><p>Any operational weaknesses, that may be found in commercial systems, are a matter for the ports themselves to resolve.</p>",,"Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985017/answer",,,,,,"2018-10-24T13:15:13.377Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985017/answer","Biography information for Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985017/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-10","Ports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what meetings (1) ministers, and (2) officials have held with UK port-owning companies to discuss (a) preparations for Brexit, and (b) current operational weaknesses.","false","Biography information for Lord Mendelsohn",,"Lord Mendelsohn","HL10560"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985018","Department for Transport","false","2018-10-23","<p>Her Majesty's Government is seeking to negotiate arrangements whereby trade will flow as frictionlessly as possible, facilitating continuing growth in unit load traffic and port productivity. In the event of a no-deal outcome, the aim is to ensure that UK border controls at the frontier enable traffic to continue to flow efficiently through our ports.</p>",,"Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985018/answer",,,,,,"2018-10-23T11:02:15.557Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985018/answer","Biography information for Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985018/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-10","Ports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of (1) the impact of Brexit on the productivity of the UK's ports, and (2) the likely impact on the UK's ports of a no-deal Brexit.","false","Biography information for Lord Mendelsohn",,"Lord Mendelsohn","HL10561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985019","Department for Transport","false","2018-10-24","<p>The efficiency of operational IT infrastructure is a commercial matter for each port. HMG has however assessed cyber security at several key ports. In addition, we have published guidance for industry as a whole. The Network and Information Systems Regulations, which came into force in May 2018, have placed mandatory cyber security requirements on the most critical UK operators.</p><p>HMRC and Border Force are familiar with the IT arrangements in relation to the CHIEF system, and its successor, CDS, for handling border control declarations.</p>",,"Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985019/answer",,,,,,"2018-10-24T12:34:18.837Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985019/answer","Biography information for Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985019/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-10","Ports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what is their assessment of the efficiency of IT infrastructure at UK ports; and what plans they have to support improvements in IT infrastructure at UK ports in time for Brexit.","false","Biography information for Lord Mendelsohn",,"Lord Mendelsohn","HL10562"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985020","Department for Transport","false","2018-10-24","<p>Operations at the ports of Felixstowe and at Southampton Container Terminal are matters for the operators themselves in consultation with customers and port users, including SMEs. I understand that the situation at Felixstowe has now improved following difficulties with the 'nGen' system, and that congestion recently affecting Southampton was expected to be transient.</p><p> </p><p>UK container port capacity overall is easily sufficient to meet demand in the pre-Christmas period, and there is also scope for further consented expansion to meet future growth in global trade including the largest vessels currently in world fleets.</p>",,"Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985020/answer",,,,,"HL10564 ; HL10565","2018-10-24T12:34:06.18Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985020/answer","Biography information for Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985020/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-10","Ports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the impact on productivity in shipside operations at the Port of Felixstowe of IT implementation issues and of problems at the port of Southampton; and what support they have offered.","false","Biography information for Lord Mendelsohn",,"Lord Mendelsohn","HL10563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985021","Department for Transport","false","2018-10-24","<p>Operations at the ports of Felixstowe and at Southampton Container Terminal are matters for the operators themselves in consultation with customers and port users, including SMEs. I understand that the situation at Felixstowe has now improved following difficulties with the 'nGen' system, and that congestion recently affecting Southampton was expected to be transient.</p><p> </p><p>UK container port capacity overall is easily sufficient to meet demand in the pre-Christmas period, and there is also scope for further consented expansion to meet future growth in global trade including the largest vessels currently in world fleets.</p>",,"Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985021/answer",,,,,"HL10563 ; HL10565","2018-10-24T12:34:06.103Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985021/answer","Biography information for Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985021/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-10","Ports","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether, in the light of experience at the Port of Felixstowe, they intend to write to UK Port companies to encourage better planning on IT and other investment changes to ensure consistent UK port capacity in the pre-Christmas period.","false","Biography information for Lord Mendelsohn",,"Lord Mendelsohn","HL10564"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985022","Department for Transport","false","2018-10-24","<p>Operations at the ports of Felixstowe and at Southampton Container Terminal are matters for the operators themselves in consultation with customers and port users, including SMEs. I understand that the situation at Felixstowe has now improved following difficulties with the 'nGen' system, and that congestion recently affecting Southampton was expected to be transient.</p><p> </p><p>UK container port capacity overall is easily sufficient to meet demand in the pre-Christmas period, and there is also scope for further consented expansion to meet future growth in global trade including the largest vessels currently in world fleets.</p>",,"Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985022/answer",,,,,"HL10563 ; HL10564","2018-10-24T12:34:06.243Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985022/answer","Biography information for Baroness Sugg","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/985022/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-10-10","Felixstowe Port: ICT","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what is their assessment of the impact the Port of Felixstowe’s IT problems are having on small and medium-sized enterprises.","false","Biography information for Lord Mendelsohn",,"Lord Mendelsohn","HL10565"
