"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984553","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-10-17","<p>The procurement of the Fleet Solid Support ships through international competition reflects the fact that they are Naval Auxiliary Support Ships and not warships. We are therefore required by law to procure them through international competition, under our obligations set out in the Defence and Security Public Contracts Regulations 2011 and as outlined in the National Shipbuilding Strategy.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984553/answer",,,,,,"2018-10-17T16:50:14.86Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984553/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/984553/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-09","Navy: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether (a) his Department or (b) HM Treasury determines that planned orders for future fleet solid support ships will be subject to international competition.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","177206"
